EventItemMatterName: Recognizing and supporting the efforts of organizations that work to increase consumer awareness of and commitment to poor farming communities around the world through Fair Trade.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to comprehensive tracking of firefighting response times.
EventItemMatterName: Comprehensive tracking of firefighting response times.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Department of Correctional Services to end MCI’s exorbitant and exclusive telephone contract, which forces inmates to pay a per-call connection fee of $3.00 plus sixteen cents a minute when calling family or friends, and to instead provide just and reasonably priced calling options for inmates.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Dep't of Correctional Services to end MCI’s exorbitant and exclusive telephone contract.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the appropriate committee of the Council of the City of New York to conduct hearings on the findings of the October 15, 2004 Report of the National Institutes of Health, concluding that counseling programs for families and youth-at-risk are more effective in deterring adolescent violence than “get tough” programs, group detention facilities, treating juveniles as adults in the criminal justice system and adult lecturing programs.
EventItemMatterName: Conduct hearings on the findings of the October 15, 2004 Report of the National Institutes of Health.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the City Department of Transportation to immediately expand its Safe Routes to School program to every elementary school in New York City to prevent traffic injuries and deaths of children.
EventItemMatterName: DOT to immediately expand its Safe Routes to School program.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the appropriate committee of the Council of the city of New York to hold an oversight hearing regarding Homebase, the new $12 million homelessness prevention program of the Department of Homeless Services and calling for the expansion of Homebase citywide.
EventItemMatterName: Hold an oversight hearing regarding Homebase.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution concerning the establishment of the 161st Street Business Improvement District in the Borough of the Bronx and setting the date, time and place for the public hearing to hear all persons interested in the establishment of such district.
EventItemMatterName: 161st Street Business Improvement District, the Bronx.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the purchase of energy efficient products, and to repeal subdivisions a, c, d, e and f of section 6-127 of such code.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to reporting on releases from and the status of underground storage tank systems.
EventItemMatterName: Reporting on releases from and the status of underground storage tank systems.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to increasing the penalties for a violation of a stop work order and for work performed without a permit, and to repeal paragraph 5 of subdivision g of section 26-248 of such code, relating to working without a permit and refusing to stop.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing the penalties for a violation of a stop work order and for work performed without a permit.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
